Question: 
An array arr is a mountain if the following properties hold:

arr.length >= 3
There exists some i with 0 < i < arr.length - 1 such that:

arr[0] < arr[1] < ... < arr[i - 1] < arr[i]
arr[i] > arr[i + 1] > ... > arr[arr.length - 1]


Return the index i such that arr is a mountain and arr[i] is the peak of the mountain.



Example 1:

Input: arr = [0,1,0]

Output: 1
Example 2:

Input: arr = [0,2,1,0]

Output: 1
Example 3:

Input: arr = [0,10,5,2]

Output: 1
 

Constraints:

3 <= arr.length <= 105
0 <= arr[i] <= 106


Solution:

Approuch:Binary Search

Thinking : only check the element ig the mid element if mid elemnt is greater than mid+1 
then move the left mid +1 otherwise move the right = mid

class Solution {
    public int peakIndexInMountainArray(int[] arr) {
     int left = 0;
     int right = arr.length-1;
     while(left<right){
        int mid =(left+right)/2;
        if(arr[mid]<arr[mid+1]) left = mid+1;
        else right = mid;
     }
     return left; 
    }
}

Time Complexity : O(log n)
Space Complexity : O(1)
